'''''Trouble''''' is the second album by the [[United Kingdom|British]] [[pop music|pop]] [[musical ensemble|group]] [[Sailor (band)|'''Sailor''']], formed in 1973 and best known in the 1970s for their [[hit single]]s "A Glass of Champagne" and "Girls, Girls, Girls" (both featured on this album), written by the group's Norwegian lead singer and 12-string guitar player, [[Georg Kajanus]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicvf.com/Sailor.art|title=Sailor Songs ••• Top Songs / Chart Singles Discography ••• Music VF, US & UK hits charts|publisher=}}</ref> The album reached #45 in the UK charts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/15561/sailor/|title=SAILOR|publisher=}}</ref>

==Track listing<ref name="Original album sleeve notes">Original album sleeve notes</ref>==

:All words and music by Georg Kajanus

